statement_text:
For all integers $k,d\geq 1$ there exists $\ell>0$ with the following property. Let $G$ be a graph and let $S,T\subseteq V(G)$. Then either
\begin{itemize}
\item there are $k$ paths between $S,T$, pairwise at distance at least $d$; or
\item there is a set $X\subseteq V(G)$ with $|X|\leq k-1$ such that every path between $S,T$ contains a vertex with distance at most $\ell$ from some member of $X$.
\end{itemize}
